Text: KEMP: Before I answer that, Jim, let me just say it is disgraceful, the campaign being waged to scare the American senior citizens, in this state and my home state of, well, New York and California, about Medicare.
Speech: Before I answer that, Jim, let me just say it is disgraceful, the campaign being waged to scare the American senior citizens, in this state and my home state of, well, New York and California, about Medicare.

Speech: One other one in there, isn't there?
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: KEMP: about Medicare Yeah, Maryland now.
Speech: about Medicare Yeah, Maryland now.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: The amount of money being spent to try to mislead the American people is demagoguery, and only in the Clinton White House and in Al Gore's mind could an increase in spending per capita on a senior citizen from $4800 in 1996 to $7200 over the next five years be considered a cut.
Speech: The amount of money being spent to try to mislead the American people is demagoguery, and only in the Clinton White House and in Al Gore's mind could an increase in spending per capita on a senior citizen from $4800 in 1996 to $7200 over the next five years be considered a cut.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Does anybody think that Bob Dole, who almost gave his life for his country, who has served in the Senate, who helped save Social Security, crawled out of a fox hole on Riva Ridge in Northern Italy in 1945 to save a wounded radioman?
Speech: Does anybody think that Bob Dole, who almost gave his life for his country, who has served in the Senate, who helped save Social Security, crawled out of a fox hole on Riva Ridge in Northern Italy in 1945 to save a wounded radioman?
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Does anybody think in this country that he could possibly want to move our country ahead and leave anybody behind?
Speech: Does anybody think in this country that he could possibly want to move our country ahead and leave anybody behind?
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Of course, we can balance the budget.
Speech: Of course, we can balance the budget.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Of course, we have to hold down the growth in entitlement spending.
Speech: Of course, we have to hold down the growth in entitlement spending.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: But clearly, you cannot balance the budget, Jim, without growing this economy.
Speech: But clearly, you cannot balance the budget, Jim, without growing this economy.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: It's only growing at about two-and-a-half percent.
Speech: It's only growing at about two-and-a-half percent.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: We should double the rate of growth and double the size of American economy.
Speech: We should double the rate of growth and double the size of American economy.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: This means more jobs, more wealth, more income and more capital, particularly for our nation's poor and those left behind.
Speech: This means more jobs, more wealth, more income and more capital, particularly for our nation's poor and those left behind.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: GORE: Mr. Lehrer, our balanced budget plan extends the Medicare Trust Fund ten years into the future.
Speech: Mr. Lehrer, our balanced budget plan extends the Medicare Trust Fund ten years into the future.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: A commission is fine, but a commission would not do any good if we adopted this risky $550-billion tax scheme.
Speech: A commission is fine, but a commission would not do any good if we adopted this risky $550-billion tax scheme.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: The word "scary" has been used.
Speech: The word "scary" has been used.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: A couple of days ago I went with Governor Lawton Chiles, who was here, to Sarasota to the Friendship Senior Center.
Speech: A couple of days ago I went with Governor Lawton Chiles, who was here, to Sarasota to the Friendship Senior Center.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I talked with a woman there named Dorothy Wornell and she said, "You know, we may not be as sophisticated as some of those people in Washington, but we can add and subtract."
Speech: I talked with a woman there named Dorothy Wornell and she said, "You know, we may not be as sophisticated as some of those people in Washington, but we can add and subtract."

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Here are the numbers she's adding and subtracting.
Speech: Here are the numbers she's adding and subtracting.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Bob Dole's plan would have already imposed an extra $268 on the average Medicare receiving couple, and his plan would have doubled deductibles.
Speech: Bob Dole's plan would have already imposed an extra $268 on the average Medicare receiving couple, and his plan would have doubled deductibles.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: It would have cost an extra $1,700 over the lifetime of his plan and eliminated nursing home standards and guarantees of nursing home care for seniors.
Speech: It would have cost an extra $1,700 over the lifetime of his plan and eliminated nursing home standards and guarantees of nursing home care for seniors.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: Bill Clinton prevented it from happening.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We will never allow that to happen.
Speech: We will never allow that to happen.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: KEMP: Jim, Medicare is too important to senior citizens around this country to play the type of politics that is being played on this issue.
Speech: Jim, Medicare is too important to senior citizens around this country to play the type of politics that is being played on this issue.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: It is losing $8 billion as we stand here tonight.
Speech: It is losing $8 billion as we stand here tonight.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: By the President's own trustees of Medicare, three members of which serve in his cabinet, it will be losing $23 billion a year by 1998.
Speech: By the President's own trustees of Medicare, three members of which serve in his cabinet, it will be losing $23 billion a year by 1998.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Something must be done.
Speech: Something must be done.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Bob Dole is -- has suggested a commission, but, clearly, you cannot save Medicare, Social Security, or any program for the social welfare net of American people, under which they should not be allowed to fall, unless we grow this economy at least twice the rate it is growing today.
Speech: Bob Dole is -- has suggested a commission, but, clearly, you cannot save Medicare, Social Security, or any program for the social welfare net of American people, under which they should not be allowed to fall, unless we grow this economy at least twice the rate it is growing today.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: That is the issue, not scaring people in America.
Speech: That is the issue, not scaring people in America.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: GORE: Well, as I said before, he used much harsher language when he talked about Bob Dole.
Speech: Well, as I said before, he used much harsher language when he talked about Bob Dole.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: He said that Bob Dole's solution for every single problem was to increase taxes.
Speech: He said that Bob Dole's solution for every single problem was to increase taxes.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: He said just two years ago that the Bob Dole tax increase of 1982 was the largest tax increase in the history of the world, but let's get to the point.
Speech: He said just two years ago that the Bob Dole tax increase of 1982 was the largest tax increase in the history of the world, but let's get to the point.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Medicare has been adjusted 23 times since it was created in 1965.
Speech: Medicare has been adjusted 23 times since it was created in 1965.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Bob Dole, incidentally, just bragged this year that he was one of only 12 people who voted against the creation of Medicare in the first place.
Speech: Bob Dole, incidentally, just bragged this year that he was one of only 12 people who voted against the creation of Medicare in the first place.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I don't think he's -- he didn't believe in it then, and the plan that he promoted last year would have certainly been devastating to Medicare.
Speech: I don't think he's -- he didn't believe in it then, and the plan that he promoted last year would have certainly been devastating to Medicare.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Again, don't take my word for it.
Speech: Again, don't take my word for it.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: The American Hospital Association said it could have closed 700 hospitals.
Speech: The American Hospital Association said it could have closed 700 hospitals.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: The Catholic Health Association, the AARP, and many other groups who pay careful attention to Medicare said that the Dole/Gingrich plan on Medicare would have led to deep cuts, possibly set up a two-tiered system, and would have ended the kind of Medicare system that we have.
Speech: The Catholic Health Association, the AARP, and many other groups who pay careful attention to Medicare said that the Dole/Gingrich plan on Medicare would have led to deep cuts, possibly set up a two-tiered system, and would have ended the kind of Medicare system that we have.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Our plan extends Medicare ten years into the future.
Speech: Our plan extends Medicare ten years into the future.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We will always protect Medicare within the context of a balanced budget plan.
Speech: We will always protect Medicare within the context of a balanced budget plan.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: KEMP: Folks, they have no plan.
Speech: Folks, they have no plan.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: They have absolutely no plan.
Speech: They have absolutely no plan.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: The President himself suggested that the reduction in the growth of Medicare over the next five or six years ought to be held to 6 percent under the Republican plan, irrespective of the numbers, it will grow at 7 or even more percent, but that is beside the point.
Speech: The President himself suggested that the reduction in the growth of Medicare over the next five or six years ought to be held to 6 percent under the Republican plan, irrespective of the numbers, it will grow at 7 or even more percent, but that is beside the point.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: What has to be discussed is how we, as a nation, are going to create the size of an economy, create a national wealth that would at least double this 6 or 7 trillion economy.
Speech: What has to be discussed is how we, as a nation, are going to create the size of an economy, create a national wealth that would at least double this 6 or 7 trillion economy.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: We would have $6 trillion in 15 years extra wealth for the American people.
Speech: We would have $6 trillion in 15 years extra wealth for the American people.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Another trillion dollars of revenue, with which to save Medicare and Social Security.
Speech: Another trillion dollars of revenue, with which to save Medicare and Social Security.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: And you can't do it with a tax code and a regulatory code and people suing each other with frivolous suits, as this administration is allowing to happen.
Speech: And you can't do it with a tax code and a regulatory code and people suing each other with frivolous suits, as this administration is allowing to happen.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: That has to change, and it will under Bob Dole and Jack Kemp.
Speech: That has to change, and it will under Bob Dole and Jack Kemp.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: I think Mr. Kemp has unintentionally made a mistake in saying that President Clinton called for reduction of -- to 6 percent or whatever you said.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I believe you were referring to the "Money" magazine interview, and the publisher of "Money" magazine just sent Mr. Kemp a letter two days ago asking him to please stop inaccurately citing "Money" magazine.
Speech: I believe you were referring to the "Money" magazine interview, and the publisher of "Money" magazine just sent Mr. Kemp a letter two days ago asking him to please stop inaccurately citing "Money" magazine.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: It is not what the President said.
Speech: It is not what the President said.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: It is not the President's position.
Speech: It is not the President's position.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Let me make clear what his position is.
Speech: Let me make clear what his position is.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We will save Medicare.
Speech: We will save Medicare.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We will stop efforts to hurt Medicare, and we'll do it within a balanced budget plan.
Speech: We will stop efforts to hurt Medicare, and we'll do it within a balanced budget plan.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: I will answer the question, but for the record, I would like to release the letter to our friends in the press of the letter I got from "Money" magazine, suggesting that Bill Clinton wanted and did lower the cost of living allowance for senior citizens as a way of reducing Social Security.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Putting that aside, the -- we recognize there's no consensus in America.
Speech: Putting that aside, the -- we recognize there's no consensus in America.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: This country is split between those who call themselves pro-choice, and I'm sure, very sincerely, and those of us who call ourselves pro-life, this is a very emotional issue.
Speech: This country is split between those who call themselves pro-choice, and I'm sure, very sincerely, and those of us who call ourselves pro-life, this is a very emotional issue.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: I'm sure it is for a woman.
Speech: I'm sure it is for a woman.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: It certainly is for those of us like my wife and myself who have three adopted grandchildren.
Speech: It certainly is for those of us like my wife and myself who have three adopted grandchildren.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: We thank God every night of our life that a young woman was given a choice, was given the opportunity to choose life.
Speech: We thank God every night of our life that a young woman was given a choice, was given the opportunity to choose life.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: This country should not be torn asunder over this debate, it has to be carried out with civility and respect, and Bob and I believe it can be.
Speech: This country should not be torn asunder over this debate, it has to be carried out with civility and respect, and Bob and I believe it can be.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: But we should recognize that every human life is precious and there should be all of the protection that we can give for an unborn human being.
Speech: But we should recognize that every human life is precious and there should be all of the protection that we can give for an unborn human being.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: And to think that in this country, for every three births, there is one abortion.
Speech: And to think that in this country, for every three births, there is one abortion.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: But even worse than that, as ugly as that might be -- and I know it's a tragedy to many people both on the pro-choice and pro-life position -- we have a President who vetoed a congressional ban on the ugly and gruesome practice of snatching life away from a child just moments before he or she enters the world.
Speech: But even worse than that, as ugly as that might be -- and I know it's a tragedy to many people both on the pro-choice and pro-life position -- we have a President who vetoed a congressional ban on the ugly and gruesome practice of snatching life away from a child just moments before he or she enters the world.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: That is unacceptable.
Speech: That is unacceptable.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: GORE: President Clinton has made it clear that he will sign legislation outlawing procedures such as this if there is a -- an exception to protect the health of the mother where serious health consequences, such as the inability to have any further children, are involved and her doctor advises her so.
Speech: President Clinton has made it clear that he will sign legislation outlawing procedures such as this if there is a -- an exception to protect the health of the mother where serious health consequences, such as the inability to have any further children, are involved and her doctor advises her so.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: What is really at stake here is whether or not women will have the right to choose.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: The platform on which Mr. Kemp and Senator Dole are running pledges a constitutional amendment to take away a woman's right to choose and to have the government come in and order that woman to do what the government says, no matter what the circumstances.
Speech: The platform on which Mr. Kemp and Senator Dole are running pledges a constitutional amendment to take away a woman's right to choose and to have the government come in and order that woman to do what the government says, no matter what the circumstances.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Mr. Kemp has voted 47 out of 47 times to have such an amendment and to restrict this completely, no matter what the circumstances, even where rape and incest is involved.
Speech: Mr. Kemp has voted 47 out of 47 times to have such an amendment and to restrict this completely, no matter what the circumstances, even where rape and incest is involved.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We will never allow a woman's right to choose to be taken away.
Speech: We will never allow a woman's right to choose to be taken away.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: KEMP: There is no consensus.
Speech: There is no consensus.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: A constitutional amendment would not pass.
Speech: A constitutional amendment would not pass.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: We must use persuasion, not intimidation.
Speech: We must use persuasion, not intimidation.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Bob Dole and Jack Kemp will try to remind the American people of what a tremendous asset our children are and why there should be protection for innocent human life, including that of the unborn.
Speech: Bob Dole and Jack Kemp will try to remind the American people of what a tremendous asset our children are and why there should be protection for innocent human life, including that of the unborn.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: But to think that this administration vetoed the one chance they had to ban that practice without working with people in the Congress who would have loved to have had the opportunity to stop that gruesome practice is just unacceptable to the American people.
Speech: But to think that this administration vetoed the one chance they had to ban that practice without working with people in the Congress who would have loved to have had the opportunity to stop that gruesome practice is just unacceptable to the American people.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: And Bob Dole would never have vetoed that ban on partial-birth abortions in the third trimester of a woman's pregnancy.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: The fighting has stopped in Bosnia.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: President Bill Clinton showed tremendous courage, vision, wisdom, and leadership in having our country take the lead in rallying our allies, bringing the warring factions together in Dayton, Ohio, and hammering out a peace agreement that has ended the war in Bosnia.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We hope that it will stay over with.
Speech: We hope that it will stay over with.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Elections having just been held.
Speech: Elections having just been held.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: There is great progress towards peace and reconciliation in Bosnia.
Speech: There is great progress towards peace and reconciliation in Bosnia.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We ought to be very proud of our soldiers who have played such a critical role in bringing about this peace in Bosnia.
Speech: We ought to be very proud of our soldiers who have played such a critical role in bringing about this peace in Bosnia.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: It's not the only case where Bill Clinton has provided such leadership.
Speech: It's not the only case where Bill Clinton has provided such leadership.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We have restored democracy to Haiti, with scarcely a shot being fired.
Speech: We have restored democracy to Haiti, with scarcely a shot being fired.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We have seen movement towards reconciliation in Northern Ireland and in the Middle East.
Speech: We have seen movement towards reconciliation in Northern Ireland and in the Middle East.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: The Bible says there will always be wars and rumors of wars.
Speech: The Bible says there will always be wars and rumors of wars.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: As the President said the other night, there will always be troubles in this ol' world, but the United States of America can be counted on to provide the vision that the world looks for from the United States of America.
Speech: As the President said the other night, there will always be troubles in this ol' world, but the United States of America can be counted on to provide the vision that the world looks for from the United States of America.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Bill Clinton, as President, has provided that kind of leadership.
Speech: Bill Clinton, as President, has provided that kind of leadership.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: We are more secure and stronger today because of Bill Clinton's handling of foreign policy.
Speech: We are more secure and stronger today because of Bill Clinton's handling of foreign policy.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: Bob Dole supported the deployment of troops in Bosnia, but the problem with the foreign policy of this administration, there is none.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: It is ambiguous, it is contradictory.
Speech: It is ambiguous, it is contradictory.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: It is precipitous to go into Iraq with bombing before we had even consulted with our allies.
Speech: It is precipitous to go into Iraq with bombing before we had even consulted with our allies.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: To think that Sam Nunn of Georgia or Colin Powell helped put together the coalition in the Persian Gulf were not even consulted.
Speech: To think that Sam Nunn of Georgia or Colin Powell helped put together the coalition in the Persian Gulf were not even consulted.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: It was not only precipitous, it was a sign, not of strength, but of weakness.
Speech: It was not only precipitous, it was a sign, not of strength, but of weakness.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: What's worse, they declared victory.
Speech: What's worse, they declared victory.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: They've declared victory in every deployment.
Speech: They've declared victory in every deployment.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: We've had more deployments in four years than any previous four years I can think of, and I'm 61 years of age.
Speech: We've had more deployments in four years than any previous four years I can think of, and I'm 61 years of age.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: It's unbelievable that ambiguity can be called foreign policy.
Speech: It's unbelievable that ambiguity can be called foreign policy.
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Let me say what a friend told me, and I believed it for my whole career, weakness is provocative and our message should be clear.

Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: And that's what our message would be to the world under Bob Dole as Commander-in-Chief of the United States of America.
Speech: And that's what our message would be to the world under Bob Dole as Commander-in-Chief of the United States of America.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: We did, of course, consult with our allies before we bombed Saddam Hussein, but sometimes the United States has to take unilateral action when our interests are at stake.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: We pray that democracy comes to Haiti, but so far, the message from Haiti is quite ambiguous, notwithstanding the declaration of victory by this administration.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: The fact is, we restored democracy to Haiti.
Speech: The fact is, we restored democracy to Haiti.

Speech: When I say "restored" actually, it's the first real democracy that Haiti has ever had.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: And it happened with scarcely any shots being fired.
Speech: And it happened with scarcely any shots being fired.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I was in the Oval Office the night when President Clinton dispatched our troops from Ft. Bragg.
Speech: I was in the Oval Office the night when President Clinton dispatched our troops from Ft. Bragg.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: It was a tense moment.
Speech: It was a tense moment.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: The planes were in the air and our negotiators were talking with the dictator down there.
Speech: The planes were in the air and our negotiators were talking with the dictator down there.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: And when that dictator got the news from his spies outside the gate that all these planes were taking off, he said, let's get out of here.
Speech: And when that dictator got the news from his spies outside the gate that all these planes were taking off, he said, let's get out of here.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: That's how it was done.
Speech: That's how it was done.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: It was one of the most deft uses of diplomacy and military force in combination that you will find anywhere in the annals of the history of this country.
Speech: It was one of the most deft uses of diplomacy and military force in combination that you will find anywhere in the annals of the history of this country.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I was so proud of our President in the way he handled that, and the result, so far, is excellent.
Speech: I was so proud of our President in the way he handled that, and the result, so far, is excellent.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: And we hope and pray that it will remain that way.
Speech: And we hope and pray that it will remain that way.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: Many more results like Bosnia and Haiti and Mexico, and the Middle East, and we won't have much success.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: One of the most serious -- one of the most serious problems was the tremendous effort by this administration to force on Mexico a devaluation of their peso.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: The economy has dropped by almost 40 to 50 percent.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: Then we go in and bail them out.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: We caused the problem, then we have to bail them out.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: We should have a foreign policy that's predicated upon trade, on spreading democracy, by giving people opportunities to trade freely with us, and making sure that everybody recognizes a rule of the Golden Rule, "To do unto others to have them do unto you."
Speech: We should have a foreign policy that's predicated upon trade, on spreading democracy, by giving people opportunities to trade freely with us, and making sure that everybody recognizes a rule of the Golden Rule, "To do unto others to have them do unto you."
Speaker: KEMP
Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: Diplomacy first, and don't bomb before breakfast.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: No, that's not right.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: No, when there was a crisis involving the Mexican peso, again, President Bill Clinton showed bold and dynamic leadership.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: He agreed with the President.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Name: Albert A. Gore

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: He could not get a majority in the Senate, and Speaker Gingrich could not get a majority in the house to go on record in support of it.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: So, the President, as presidents often have to do, went alone and did the right thing.
Speech: So, the President, as presidents often have to do, went alone and did the right thing.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: You know, people said it was a big risk at that time.
Speech: You know, people said it was a big risk at that time.
Speaker: GORE
Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: We've ended up making a $500 million profit.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: All of the loans have been paid back.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: We're using that $500 million to further reduce the deficit.

Speech: It's come down 60 percent already.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: It's going down even more toward a balanced budget, and this is helping.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: It's unbelievable that we could cause a drop in the standard of living of a friendly country like Mexico by nearly 40 to 50 percent.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: Unemployment goes up, we send U.S. tax dollars and IMF monies to Mexico, and we make a profit.
Speech: Unemployment goes up, we send U.S. tax dollars and IMF monies to Mexico, and we make a profit.

Text: At that level, that is -- gives new meaning to the word "profitability" for U.S. foreign policy.
Speech: At that level, that is -- gives new meaning to the word "profitability" for U.S. foreign policy.

Text: The pain, the suffering, the unemployment, the bankruptcies, the loss of the standard of living, the people who have had to come across the border of California, Arizona, New Mexico and Texas if that's our foreign policy for the third-world or Latin America, I believe more than ever, we have to elect a president who understands trade, who understands honest money, who understands private enterprise, who understands democratic capitalism, not socialism caused by the IMF and the Clinton administration.
Speech: The pain, the suffering, the unemployment, the bankruptcies, the loss of the standard of living, the people who have had to come across the border of California, Arizona, New Mexico and Texas if that's our foreign policy for the third-world or Latin America, I believe more than ever, we have to elect a president who understands trade, who understands honest money, who understands private enterprise, who understands democratic capitalism, not socialism caused by the IMF and the Clinton administration.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: Well, I fail to understand the basis of the charge that we caused the monetary crisis in Mexico.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: They managed their own monetary policy.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: Years ago, we used to hear this phrase in American politics, the "Blame America First" crowd.
Speech: Years ago, we used to hear this phrase in American politics, the "Blame America First" crowd.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: I never liked that phrase, but if it was going to be applied today, it would have to be applied to this statement.
Speech: I never liked that phrase, but if it was going to be applied today, it would have to be applied to this statement.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: The United States of America shouldn't be blamed for the management of Mexico's monetary policy.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Name: Albert A. Gore

Name: Albert A. Gore

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: They paid us back, and we got a dividend in the process.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: That's dangerous and it's provocative.
Speech: That's dangerous and it's provocative.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: And the mixed message, the ambiguities of U.S. foreign policy, uh are -- I believe, and Bob Dole believes, is causing not only problems for this country throughout the world, but particularly here at home.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: It should be predicated upon the defense needs, the security needs, the strategic needs of the United States of America, and that's how they'll be made under Bob Dole as president.

Speech: Well, first of all, there are virtually no large differences in the defense budgets put forward by President Clinton and put forward by the majority in the Congress in the last two years.

Speech: There is a huge difference in our economic plan.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Text: This risky $550-billion tax scheme that I talked about earlier is said by the Concord Coalition, including Republicans like Pete Peterson and Warren Rudman, to pose a threat to our nation's ability to have a sensible defense budget in the future.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Speech: We have a balanced budget plan that protects the defense budget, also Medicare, Medicaid, education, the environment, and give tax -- gives tax cuts to middle-income families.

Speech: The environment faces dire threats from the kind of legislation that Senator Dole and Speaker Newt Gingrich tried to pass by shutting down the government and attempting to force President Clinton to accept it.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: This is the most overregulated, overly litigated economy in our nation's history.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Text: That will change, because we believe in democratic capitalism for everybody.
Speech: That will change, because we believe in democratic capitalism for everybody.

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: There are lots of jobs to be created in cleaning up the environment.

Speech: They don't want them to live next to toxic waste sites.

Speech: When the United States of America takes the lead in protecting the environment, we do right by our children, and we also create new business opportunities, new jobs, new sources of prosperity for the United States of America, and we're going about it in a common sense way.

Name: Albert A. Gore

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Name: Jack F. Kemp

Speech: Well, it takes values that recognize the importance of the environment.

Speech: We're eliminating 16,000 pages of regulations.
